[MODEL CACHE STORAGE BOUNDARY DEFINITION]
Expected Underlying Structural Format: Keras HDF5 (Hierarchical Data Format v5) Object representation containing complete system architecture configuration arrays, model layer topologies, compile specifications, and optimized optimization weights arrays serialized via TensorFlow 2.1x serialization bindings.

To replace this documentation vector with production-ready operational binaries:
1. Compile your final TensorFlow pipeline model.
2. Execute serialization using the instruction sequence: `model.save('backend/ml/models_cache/cnn_disease_v1.h5')`.
